Definition: aphasia in which the lesion is assumed to be in the association tracts connecting the various language centers in the brain
Example: patient's have difficulty repeating a sentence just heard
Synonyms: associative_aphasia, aphasia, in, which, the, lesion, is, assumed, to, be, association, tracts, connecting, various, language, centers, brain, patient, s, have, difficulty, repeating, a, sentence, just, heard
Category: noun.state
